\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , he came at last upon a rocky mountain with a large cave at the foot of it and a large stone over the entrance. After removing the stone and going in, eager to explore the unknown with a human curiosity, he found a spacious chamber, with an opening to the sky above covered over by spreading branches of an ancient palm tree. There was a sparkling spring there, from which a stream overflowed through a little opening, and soaked away into the earth. There were also a few little buildings near the foot of the mountain containing the knives and anvils and mallets used to strike coins; Egyptian writings tell us that this used to be the site of a secret minting factory at the time when Antony and Cleopatra were together.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pyetle took Mandrameen\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s outstretched hand and the boy helped him up. Pyetle was surprised to feel a sinewy strength in the lad; he was a bit scrawny and had a bookish look about him, with a weak chin and a scholar\u8217\'92s neck. He\u8217\'92d seen the Mandrameen ruffling through some papers earlier. He\u8217\'92d assumed the boy was something of a camp follower, but this close he noticed the boy\u8217\'92s belt was actually a corded Jandrian sling, patterned for war. Mandrameen\u8217\'92s firm grip suggested expertise.}
